cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.SY, cs.MM 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it deals with modeling and simulating network traffic. It could also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) as it discusses the Hurst parameter and Whittle's estimator. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as network traffic is a key component of social networks. It may also fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it deals with modeling and synthesizing time series data. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia) as network traffic is a key component of multimedia applications.
